originalText.text: The staff was excellent. The lady whom took my blood was awesome. I didn’t feel anything, something that can’t always be said when blood is withdrawn. She was precise, waited till the alcohol dried to prevent burning from needle….and when changing test tubes, I didn’t feel anything in my arm. Great experience and I would recommend this lab to my family and friends.

originalText.text: The staff is fast and courteous and skilled. I had blood test. I have very small veins that often are hard to locate. Today's phlebotonist found it right away and the injection was painless!

originalText.text: I experienced a well-tempered staff:  polite, professional, and highly efficient. They went above and beyond to obtain the correct script for my test, and I was finished in less than seven minutes!

originalText.text:
I've been to several labs when blood work was needed, both in Manhattan and Queens
Today, at 170 East 77th Steet, I was treated with kindness,  patience and professionalism by the entire staff up front.   The woman she took my blood (Jackie -- I'm reasonably sure of her name) was finished minutes after I sat down.

Everyone was more than efficient.   This is now my go-to lab.  Thanks, guys.

originalText.text: Was sent here after the doctor’s phlebotomist could not get a good blood draw on me. She had stuck me three times, with no success. I drank a cup of water, and a bottle of water, and went over to the lab. That phlebotomist had no problem at all. Quick and very efficient.
